                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "[[h3]]The HTML boilerplate[[/]]"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n  <head>\n  </head>\n\n  <body>\n    <!-- All future content goes here -->\n  </body>\n</html>"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "So, to kick things off, let’s create two components called addItem.jsx and itemList.jsx and import them into our project. "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "[[h3]]Explanation[[/]]"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "➔ The previous lines of code just create a blank page for us to work with"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "➔ <!DOCTYPE html> specifies that we are writing code in HTML"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "➔ The <html></html> blocks wrap our main HTML code"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "➔ The <head></head> blocks will wrap any links or browser descriptions we want to add"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "➔ Finally, the <body></body> is where we will be placing all our future examples"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "➔ This is what actually gets displayed on the screen"
                }
            ],
